    "We evaluate the performance by removing personalized, common, and both prompting, which is denoted as '-Personalized', '-Common', and '-Both', respectively.",
    "It is observed that both common and personalized prompts play a crucial role in improving performance for DIL tasks.",
    "Removing the common prompts leads to a decline in performance across the three tasks, as inter-domain knowledge sharing becomes impaired.",
    "Similarly, omitting the personalized prompts results in an ineffective extraction of knowledge within domains, leading to substantial performance loss.Model Parameter Analysis.",
    "We further explore the optimal layers for inserting domain prompts, as illustrated in Figure 6."
